songs.title: Miss Movin’ On (Acoustic)
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1: Camila & Lauren]
I'm breaking down, gonna start from scratch
Shake it off like an etch-a-sketch
My lips are saying goodbye
My eyes are finally dry
I'm not the way I used to be
I took the record off repeat
You killed me but I survived
And now I'm coming alive

[Pre-Chorus: Camila and Ally & Camila]
I'll never be that girl again, no-oh-oh
I'll never be that girl again, no-oh-oh

[Chorus: Lauren and Normani & Lauren and Ally & Lauren and Normani & Lauren ]
My innocence is wearing thin
But my heart is growing strong
So call me, call me, call me
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh , yeah

[Verse 2: Lauren & Dinah & (Normani)]
I broke the glass that surrounded me (surrounded me)
I ain't the way you remember me (remember me)
I was such a good girl
So fragile but no more
I jumped the fence to the other side (the other side)
My whole world was electrified (electrified)
Now I'm no longer afraid
It's Independence Day
(It's Independence Day)

[Pre-Chorus: Camila and Ally & Camila]
I'll never be that girl again, no-oh-oh
I'll never be that girl again, no-oh-oh

[Chorus: Lauren and Normani & Lauren and Ally]
My innocence is wearing thin
But my heart is growing strong
So call me, call me, call me
Miss movin' on

[Bridge: Dinah and Ally & (Normani) & Dinah]
Everything is changing
And I never wanna go back to the way it was (the way it was)
I'm finding who I am
And who I am from here on out is gonna be enough (it's gonna be enough)
It's gonna be enough

[Pre-Chorus: Normani & Ally]
I'll never be that girl again, no-oh-oh
I'll never be that girl again, oh-oh-oh

[Chorus: Lauren & All & Lauren and Ally & Lauren and Normani & (Ally) & Camila & (Normani)]
My innocence is wearing thin
But my heart is growing strong
So call me, call me, call me
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh (Oh-oh-on!)
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh (on and on and on and on and on)
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh (on and on and on and on and on)
Miss movin' on,  oh-oh-oh (on and on and on and on and on) (Hey, yeah)

[Outro: Lauren]
Yeah, I'm movin' on
